# Ship sync — docs, issues, and boards

When you ship a feature, fix a defect, or close a roadmap item, update **all** of the following in the same session:

## Repository docs

- `README.md` roadmap table (status column)
- `CHANGELOG.md` (Unreleased section)
- `docs/product/planning.md` roadmap table
- `docs/delivery/current-version-scope.md` when scope changes
- `docs/engineering/integrations.md`, `cli-reference.md`, `ci-cd.md`, `doctor-and-validation.md` when behaviour changes
- `TEAM-TESTING.md` and `packages/dna-cli/README.md` for user-facing setup flows
- `scripts/sync-roadmap-to-project.sh` status arrays if issue statuses changed

## GitHub issues

- Update issue body checklists and **Status** line (Shipped / In progress / Planned)
- Close issues when work is complete; leave open with **Remaining** checklist when partially done
- Add a closing comment referencing the commit SHA

## Project boards

- [DNA Roadmap](https://github.com/users/superhumaan/projects/3/views/1) — Shipped / In progress / Planned columns
- [DNA - Defects](https://github.com/users/superhumaan/projects/4/views/1) — Done / In progress / Backlog columns

Run `./scripts/sync-roadmap-to-project.sh` after updating status arrays. Requires `gh auth refresh -s read:project,project`.

## Do not leave stale

- `GITHUB_TOKEN`-only setup in docs when browser login (`dna github login`) is the recommended path
- Roadmap rows marked "In progress" after the work shipped
- Open GitHub issues for completed roadmap items
